## Correctness Constraints

| Concern | Detail |
|---|---|
| `groupByCategory` total | Incremental `+=` gives the same floating-point sum as `reduce` because additions are in the same left-to-right order |
| `findDuplicates` key format | Key is `${userId}\|${amount}\|${date}` — identical to original (raw number, not rounded) |
| `calculateRunningBalance` rounding | `runningSum` is kept unrounded; `Math.round(runningSum * 100) / 100` applied per entry, exactly as the original inner loop does |
| `topSpenders` ordering | Sort is descending by `totalSpent` (same as bubble sort direction) |
| `searchTransactions` dedup | Set-based dedup is semantically equivalent; order of results preserved |

---

## Verification

```bash
